[DhtmlXQ_comment10]Mag:This was the move that GM Zhao played back in 1984. It is also deemed inappropriate now, after what happened in this game!||Contemporary studies favor P7+1 instead of C2=5, allowing black more options to develop his right flank, and to counter red's attack more precisely.[/DhtmlXQ_comment10]
[DhtmlXQ_comment11]Huang: Red sacrifices his pawn to allow his right chariot to protect the horse. Afterward, red would retreat his cannon C8-1 as a continuation of his plans, for a concerted attack.||It would not be advisable to take the pawn now.||However, if black played R8-1...||Jim: pls click on the variation on the next move to understand...[/DhtmlXQ_comment11]
